Okay! I think I found it! The errors are coming because the authentication filter is working EXACTLY as it should - it is restricting requests to the api endpoints.

To test it, I whitelisted our api endpoints and the errors go away.

So we should be good to merge in Niko's work, and we can start working on the next parts of the gameplan.

<@U05777BLCPN> an important thing we'll need to make sure we can access those endpoints when they're no longer whitelisted is to include the user session with every API request - that's what the preHandle method in the AuthenticationFilter expects.

elements.text:
Okay! I think I found it! The errors are coming because the authentication filter is working EXACTLY as it should - it is restricting requests to the api endpoints.

To test it, I whitelisted our api endpoints and the errors go away.

So we should be good to merge in Niko's work, and we can start working on the next parts of the gameplan.

an important thing we'll need to make sure we can access those endpoints when they're no longer whitelisted is to include the user session with every API request - that's what the preHandle method in the AuthenticationFilter expects.
